05/09/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The interior ministry announced that a visa-free regime between Macedonia and Albania came into force on Thursday (September 4th). 
Signed in January, the agreement took effect after ratification by the Macedonian parliament. 
It abolishes the visa requirement for citizens of Macedonia wishing to travel to Albania and vice versa. 
(Vecer, Dnevnik - 05/09/08; MIA, Telegrafi - 04/09/08)
